\section*{Reliability with Series Systems:}

The problem with series systems is that reliability quickly decreases as the number of components increases.

\section*{Reliability with Parallel Systems}

The problem with parallel systems is that the 'law of diminishing returns' operates. The rate of increase in reliability with each additional component decreases as the number of components increases.
Most systems are combinations of series and parallel systems

